results.name: Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = number of specially labeled bicolored connected graphs with k points in one color class and n-k points in the other class . "Special" means there are separate labels 1,2, ...,k and 1,2, ...,n-k for the two color classes (n >= 1, k = floor((n+1)/2), ..., n).
reference: R. W. Robinson, Numerical implementation of graph counting algorithms, AGRC Grant, Math. Dept., Univ. Newcastle, Australia, 1977.
